      {
        "id": 3080813,
        "name": "Brian Buzzini",
        "username": "B_Buzzini",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/b_buzzini/{size}/636_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-01-26T00:29:21.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2031902&amp;iNote=8929033\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2013 Bouchard P\u00e8re et Fils Corton-Le Corton</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Corton Grand Cru (1/25/2021)</em><br>\nLast had this 2yrs ago, and although a fine drink, it did seem to be coiled and not giving up the full monty just yet. Decant for air a must\u2026this bottle still quite tight and not wanting to bare it all\u2026it shows a wonderful med bodied, silky elegance\u2026very translucent, and showing all the crushed rocks and firm minerality\u2026yet there is a polished sheen that caresses the palate. More sous bois and mushroom earth showing in this\u2026to go with the red berried wild fruits\u2026licorice, raspberry puree, dried roses, sandalwood spice\u2026nice blood orange type streak of acidity livens as well. Super elegant, subtle, and persistent finish\u2026very pleasing! Can\u2019t wait till it\u2019s all open for biz! +pts <em><strong>(93 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/a/f/afbb418f5bae741842cbb2c949ccb8ed86a03635.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/afbb418f5bae741842cbb2c949ccb8ed86a03635\" title=\"\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/a/f/afbb418f5bae741842cbb2c949ccb8ed86a03635_2_375x500.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-base62-sha1=\"p4AKBnpkAOsGcPALPjVxID1fOG9\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/a/f/afbb418f5bae741842cbb2c949ccb8ed86a03635_2_375x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/a/f/afbb418f5bae741842cbb2c949ccb8ed86a03635_2_562x750.jpeg 1.5x, https: