      {
        "id": 3080994,
        "name": "\u0104\u0146\u0257\u0157\u0119\u0175 \u0136\u013c\u03cb\u01e5",
        "username": "Andrew_K",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/andrew_k/{size}/279879_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-01-26T02:47:33.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks. I had this wine a couple of weeks ago, but I guess I forgot to post the TN.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2031902&amp;iNote=8903859\"><strong>2013 Bouchard P\u00e8re et Fils Corton-Le Corton</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Corton Grand Cru (1/13/2021)</em><br>\nWarm. Spice garden nose with vanillin and floral notes. Palate is tightly coiled and needs time to express. But hints of greatness are shown with black fruit and earth framed by a bright acidity and lovely backbone. Finish is a bit tart but lingering. <em><strong>(93 pts.)</strong></em></p>",
